<li id="cite_note-Haifa-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Haifa_16-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Haifa_16-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Haifa_16-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Yael Onn, et. al., <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://books.google.com/books?id=yeVRrrJw-zAC&pg=PA1&dq=right+to+privacy+tel+aviv&hl=en&ei=T0IhTaWhEI-msQOizMWZCg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&amp;q=right%20to%20privacy%20tel%20aviv&amp;f=false"><i>Privacy in the Digital Environment</i></a> , Haifa Center of Law &amp; Technology, (2005) pp. 1-12</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Westin, A. (1968). Privacy and freedom (Fifth ed.). New York, U.S.A.: Atheneum.</span></li>
